    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-21T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/488: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-21T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 21, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 21—7:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1116. Following from American Consul General at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 19, 1 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Traffic on Taonan-Anganghsi line suspended since yesterday.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Huhai line cut in several places by Volunteers’.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>There are American missionaries at Suihua on Huhai line and at
                                Tsitsihar but at both places are Japanese troops. Japanese Consulate
                                General assured me they are in no danger.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>On September 16th consular corps suggested civil administrator
                                that local police force be augmented by 600 Europeans to be
                                stationed where foreigners reside. Chinese members police force pay
                                in arrears, unreliable.</item>
                            <label>5.</label>
                            <item>Evening of 15th large body of [anti-?] Manchukuo forces attacked,
                                besieged and looted Shuangcheng southern line Chinese Eastern
                                Railway. After being bombarded by Japanese artillery at railway
                                station they retired only to return and enter city and [<hi
                                    rend="italic">sic</hi>] on the 16th. City now in flames.
                                Yesterday morning’s south train arrived late, [from?] Changchun,
                                delay due taking up rails near Yaomin, one car derailed, no
                                casualties, train not attacked.</item>
                            <label>6.</label>
                            <item>Latest reports indicate quiet conditions Hailar and
                                Manchouli.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
